{
  "texts": [
    "To effectively handle concurrent requests, the manager employs a thread pool with a configurable number of threads (set at 8 in our prototype) for asynchronous processing.The allocation strategy is as follows.",
    "First, the manager checks any NANA rank requested by its previous user.",
    "This strategy optimizes resource usage by avoiding the need for resetting the rank, saving CPU cycle.",
    "If no suitable NANA device is found, the manager looks for a NAAV rank using a round-robin algorithm.",
    "If no NAAV ranks are available and NANA ranks exist, the manager enters a waiting state until a NANA rank becomes available."
  ]
}